---
// Static landing / about page. Lives at /about. Pure Astro, no
// client JS — the page is the same on first paint as fully loaded.
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Folio is a constraint-aware authoring tool for picture books and early-reader literature. Built for authors and speech-language pathologists. Runs in your browser, never sends your manuscript anywhere."
    />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://folio.harmonic-systems.org/about" />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:site_name" content="Folio" />
    <meta property="og:title" content="Folio — about" />
    <meta property="og:description" content="A constraint-aware authoring tool for picture books and early-reader literature. Built for authors and speech-language pathologists." />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://folio.harmonic-systems.org/about" />
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary" />
    <meta name="twitter:title" content="Folio — about" />
    <meta name="twitter:description" content="A constraint-aware authoring tool for picture books and early-reader literature." />
    <script
      is:inline
      defer
      data-domain="folio.harmonic-systems.org"
      src="https://plausible.io/js/script.js"
    ></script>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Libre+Caslon+Text:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&display=swap"
    />
    <title>Folio — about</title>
    <style>
      :root {
        --cream: #f7f1e6;
        --beige: #ece2cf;
        --taupe: #8a7c66;
        --ink: #2c2620;
        --rule: #d9cdb4;
        --ochre: #a37828;
        --rust: #9a4a2a;
      }
      * { box-sizing: border-box; }
      html, body {
        margin: 0; padding: 0;
        background: var(--cream); color: var(--ink);
        font-family: 'Libre Caslon Text', Georgia, serif;
        line-height: 1.6;
      }
      main {
        max-width: 44rem;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 4rem 1.5rem 6rem;
      }
      header.hero { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
      h1 {
        font-size: 2.4rem;
        font-weight: 500;
        margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
        letter-spacing: -0.015em;
      }
      .tagline {
        font-size: 1.15rem;
        font-style: italic;
        color: var(--taupe);
        margin: 0 0 2rem;
      }
      .cta-row {
        display: flex;
        gap: 0.75rem;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        margin-top: 1.5rem;
      }
      .cta {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 0.7rem 1.4rem;
        font-size: 1rem;
        text-decoration: none;
        border-radius: 3px;
        border: 1px solid transparent;
      }
      .cta.primary {
        background: var(--ink);
        color: var(--cream);
        border-color: var(--ink);
      }
      .cta.primary:hover { background: #1a1612; }
      .cta.secondary {
        background: transparent;
        color: var(--ink);
        border-color: var(--rule);
      }
      .cta.secondary:hover { background: var(--surface, #fff); border-color: var(--taupe); }

      section { margin: 3rem 0; }
      h2 {
        font-size: 1.3rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin: 0 0 1rem;
        letter-spacing: -0.005em;
      }
      h3 {
        font-size: 0.85rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        color: var(--taupe);
        margin: 2rem 0 0.5rem;
      }
      p { margin: 0 0 1.1rem; font-size: 1.02rem; }

      ul.audience, ul.features, ul.upcoming {
        list-style: none;
        padding: 0;
        margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
      }
      ul.audience li {
        padding: 1rem 0;
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
      }
      ul.audience li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
      ul.audience strong {
        display: block;
        font-size: 0.85rem;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
        color: var(--ochre);
        margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
      }

      ul.features {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 1rem 1.5rem;
      }
      @media (max-width: 600px) {
        ul.features { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      }
      ul.features li {
        padding: 1rem;
        background: #fff;
        border: 1px solid var(--rule);
        border-radius: 4px;
      }
      ul.features strong {
        display: block;
        margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      ul.features span { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--taupe); line-height: 1.5; }

      ul.upcoming li {
        padding: 0.5rem 0;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        color: var(--taupe);
        font-style: italic;
        border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--rule);
      }
      ul.upcoming li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
      ul.upcoming li::before { content: '· '; opacity: 0.6; font-style: normal; }

      .privacy-card {
        padding: 1.5rem;
        background: #fff;
        border: 1px solid var(--rule);
        border-left: 3px solid var(--ochre);
        border-radius: 4px;
      }
      .privacy-card p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

      footer {
        margin-top: 4rem;
        padding-top: 1.5rem;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: var(--taupe);
      }
      footer a { color: var(--taupe); }
      footer a:hover { color: var(--ink); }

      code {
        font-family: ui-monospace, 'SF Mono', Menlo, monospace;
        background: var(--beige);
        padding: 0.1rem 0.35rem;
        border-radius: 3px;
        font-size: 0.88em;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <header class="hero">
        <h1>Folio</h1>
        <p class="tagline">Restraint → creative flow. Anti-slop infrastructure for children's literature.</p>
        <div class="cta-row">
          <a href="/" class="cta primary">Open the editor →</a>
          <a href="/paste" class="cta secondary">Paste-and-analyze</a>
          <a href="/guide" class="cta secondary">How to read the analysis</a>
        </div>
      </header>

      <section>
        <p>
          Folio is a constraint-aware authoring tool for picture books and early-reader literature.
          It helps you see — <em>as you write</em> — how your manuscript lands developmentally:
          word count against the age-band target, sight-word coverage, reach words in context,
          phoneme inventory, decodability.
        </p>
        <p>
          The engine measures. It does not author. Folio will never generate manuscript text or
          illustrations on your behalf. The thesis: when the boring legibility work becomes legible
          in the background, creative flow has more room.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Who it's for</h2>
        <ul class="audience">
          <li>
            <strong>Picture-book authors</strong>
            Writing toward a specific age band — board, early picture, picture, early reader, or chapter.
            See word count, pacing across the 16 spreads, vocabulary load, and read-aloud-relevant
            phoneme structure as you write. Compare your draft against canonical fixtures (Peter Rabbit,
            Aesop, Owl &amp; Pussycat) to calibrate.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Speech-language pathologists</strong>
            The phoneme-acquisition norms in the engine come from <em>Crowe &amp; McLeod (2020), AJSLP</em> —
            the same research base SLPs already use clinically. Click any phoneme in the sidebar to
            highlight every word containing it across the whole manuscript. Useful for evaluating
            whether a candidate text fits a client's current phoneme inventory, or for designing
            intervention materials with controlled sound load.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>What's in the editor</h2>
        <ul class="features">
          <li>
            <strong>16-spread surface</strong>
            <span>Two facing pages per spread, with independent per-page composition (text-only, text-top, text-bottom, illustration-only). Grid view for overview; book view for one-spread-at-a-time at the trim's open aspect ratio.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Rich text</strong>
            <span>Bold, italic, underline, strikethrough via Lexical. Floating toolbar on selection. Markdown shortcuts as you type (<code>**bold**</code>, <code>*italic*</code>, <code>~~strike~~</code>). Soft hyphen and non-breaking space via keyboard.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Per-spread analysis</strong>
            <span>Word-count ceiling per spread (heuristic, documented), sight-word coverage, reach-word attribution, and a mini bar in the sidebar so you can see your manuscript's pacing in one downward glance.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Phonology surface</strong>
            <span>Decodability score, average syllables per word, syllable-shape breakdown, and the actual phonemes used — grouped by Crowe &amp; McLeod (2020) acquisition age, color-coded by lateness.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>In-context highlighting</strong>
            <span>Reach words underline in-place. Click any phoneme to highlight every word that contains it. Find &amp; replace tints all matches and walks current. All via the CSS Custom Highlight API — no DOM modification, no caret disruption.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Layout presets &amp; fonts</strong>
            <span>Classic facing, Mirror, Text top, Full text presets apply across all spreads without touching your text. Body fonts: Libre Caslon, Futura, Futura Bold, Atkinson Hyperlegible, Bricolage Grotesque.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Your privacy</h2>
        <div class="privacy-card">
          <p>
            Folio runs entirely in your browser. Your manuscript content never leaves your device — no
            server roundtrip, no account, no analytics about what you write.
          </p>
          <p>
            Your draft autosaves to this browser's local storage and persists across page reloads. The
            Reset button clears it. Anonymous page-view counts are recorded via
            <a href="https://plausible.io/privacy-focused-web-analytics" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Plausible</a> —
            cookieless, no personal identifiers, no cross-site tracking.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>What's coming</h2>
        <ul class="upcoming">
          <li>Syntax surfacing — sentence types and clause counts (the engine already measures them)</li>
          <li>Vocabulary tier classification (Beck / McKeown / Kucan framework via the Dale-Chall familiar-words list)</li>
          <li>Reach-word reason tooltips (tier 2 vs low-frequency)</li>
          <li>Dialogic-reading prompt suggestions</li>
          <li>Per-client phoneme acquisition profiles for SLP workflows</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <footer>
        Folio is built by <a href="https://harmonic-systems.org">Harmonic Systems</a>.
        Open source on
        <a href="https://github.com/harmonicsystems/folio" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
      </footer>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
